My team is implementing swerve drive for the first time this year. We have it driving with swerve, but it doesn’t drive straight very well, even in autonomous. We are looking for tips on how to get it to drive straight. We have code for “SysID” to characterize the drive system (KS, KV, KA), but have not done this characterization yet. Is this important for better driving? Also, should we lock the wheels in place (straight) during SysID testing?
